  "transcript": [
    {
      "turn": 1,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Hi Rohan, the excitement of a last-minute goal is unforgettable, did something like that happen recently?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 2,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Not really, but last weekend, my favorite team, Mohun Bagan, scored a last-minute goal in a local league match! It was super exciting. We won 2-1. By the way, do you follow football?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 2,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "\"Nice, Mohun Bagan pulling it off at the end is always a rush. Football moments like that stick with you. Do you watch other leagues too?\""
    },
    {
      "turn": 3,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Yeah, sometimes I watch English Premier League matches, specially Manchester United. But mostly I follow Indian Super League. My friend also love football, we often discuss matches. Speaking of which, have you seen any good movie from Bengali cinema? There are some really good ones recently."
    },
    {
      "turn": 3,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Manchester United and Mohun Bagan — both have that same edge. Football chats with friends are the best. Bengali cinema sounds interesting, I’d love to hear more — what’s one you’d recommend?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 4,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "I recommend watching *Bhooter Bhai* or *Autograph*. They are super popular and fun. But if you like something serious, *Chotoder Chobi* is also really good. Oh, by the way, do you like photography? I love clicking pictures during matches. It's amazing to capture those moments."
    },
    {
      "turn": 4,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Bhooter Bhai and Autograph sound fun, I’ll take your word for it! Chotoder Chobi has a good name too. Photography during matches must be exciting — what’s your favorite shot to take?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 5,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "My favorite shot is when the player is about to score a goal. The tension in the air is amazing. I also like capturing close-ups of fans celebrating. It’s chaotically beautiful! Do you take photos? Or is it something you’ve never tried?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 5,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "The tension before a goal is electric, I'm catching emotions mid-air! Close-ups of fans add so much heart to the story. I haven’t tried photography, but I’d love to see your shots. Do you share them anywhere?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 6,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Yeah, I sometimes share on Instagram — mostly with #MohunBagan or #ISL tags. The photos get a lot of likes, especially the ones with fans celebrating. Actually, my favorite is one where a kid was crying with joy after a win. It’s raw and real, you know? Maybe one day I’ll learn proper editing. Oh, by the way, have you seen the latest Mohun Bagan match? They almost pulled another last-minute win!"
    },
    {
      "turn": 6,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Instagram is a great space for that energy,  raw emotion and a win are hard to beat. That kid crying with joy sounds like a photo that tells a story. And Mohun Bagan’s last-minute magic never gets old. What part of the match did your friend love most?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 7,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "My friend loved the moment when the player made a solo run from midfield and scored. He was shouting the whole time, saying, \"Eita dekho!\" (You know, \"Watch this!\") It was like a dream. We still talk about it. Anyway, I should get back to my study — preparing for Bank PO is taking time. Talk to you later!"
    },
    {
      "turn": 7,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Eita dekho moments are the best ,  they stay with you forever. That solo run must have felt like a movie scene. Bank PO prep is intense, take it one step at a time. What part of the study feels toughest right now?"
    }
  ],
